Package: MacroFunctions
Type: Package
Title: Extract Macroeconomic Data for Classroom
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Gregory Green
Maintainer: The package maintainer <greegreg@gmail.com>
Description: This package extracts some basic macroeconomic data, real gdp, CPI, unemployment rate, and population.
              The functions ME_growth will manipulate a dat series to a series of growth rates so CPI becomes inflation
              data. This function also trims the data to a specific range of dates. Finally, if you want to insert recesionn markers
              into the plot of data series use the function ME_Rec.
